I know there's a couple of open issues about specific aspects of material design (like the FAB), but this is more geared towards a bigger overhaul. ownCloud's two biggest competitors, Dropbox and Google Drive, are both considered to be "Material Design" apps. Do we want ownCloud to stick with its current UI, which is closest to Dropbox, or should it move to a card layout, like Google Drive? Drive does let you switch between a list view and a grid view, so it's kind of the best of both worlds. Should ownCloud be cards by default, with the option to switch to a list view? I was thinking about doing a more formal poll, but I kind of want to get a feel for the community's opinion on the look and feel/UX of the future of the ownCloud app.

As a side note, I think that the app and the web interface should look similar/be cohesive, so there should probably be a parallel effort of moving the web interface to material as well.

